      "reasoning": "The mutation removes a critical __syncthreads() barrier at the end of the tile processing loop. This barrier ensures all threads have finished reading from shared memory (As and Bs) before the next iteration overwrites them. Without this synchronization, race conditions can occur when threads from the next iteration start loading new tiles into As/Bs while other threads are still computing with the old values. This is a classic shared memory race condition that depends on thread scheduling and warp execution order, making it non-deterministic and potentially observable with any non-zero input values. Layer 2's bitwise comparison might have missed this because race conditions can be timing-dependent and may not manifest in every execution.",
